0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbud-light-transgender-controversy-backlash-boycotts-history%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBud%20Light%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20CEO%2C%20you've%20got%20the%20general%20counsel%20in%20one%20ear%20saying%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20sued%20or%20you're%20going%20to%20use%20lose%20contracts%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alison%20Taylor%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BHigher%20Ground%3A%20How%20Business%20Can%20Do%20the%20Right%20Thing%20in%20a%20Turbulent%20World.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20you've%20got%20the%20public-affairs%20person%20in%20the%20other%20ear%20saying%20here's%20who's%20yelling%20at%20you%20on%20social%20media.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaker%20said%20companies%20were%20increasingly%20including%20mentions%20in%20their%20risk-factor%20disclosures%20of%20potential%20controversies%20around%20their%20employment%20practices%20and%20social%20initiatives.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they're%20flagging%20that%20'Hey%2C%20investors%20should%20understand%20that%20the%20DEI%20climate%20is%20in%20flux%20right%20now%20and%20we%20can't%20exactly%20predict%20what%20might%20happen.%20And%20some%20of%20our%20employment%20practices%2C%20although%20we%20believe%20they're%20fully%20legally%20compliant%2C%20may%20ultimately%20end%20up%20a%20target%20of%20litigation%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20America%20was%20nervous%20before%20the%20election%20about%20the%20political%20tides%20turning%2C%20given%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ends-affirmative-action-colleges-decision-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20ruling%20against%20affirmative%20action%20in%20college%20admissions%20and%20the%20growing%20influence%20of%20conservative%20activists%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobby-starbuck-conservative-activist-targeting-companies-dei-policies-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobby%20Starbuck%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%2C%20Trump%202.0%20has%20sent%20many%20of%20them%20into%20a%20silent%20panic%20mode.%20The%20president%20positioned%20himself%20as%20a%20fierce%20opponent%20of%20almost%20DEI%2C%20determined%20to%20root%20it%20out%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20and%2C%20if%20he%20can%20manage%20it%2C%20private%20industry.%20The%20crusade%20is%20clearly%20having%20a%20chilling%20effect%20across%20the%20business%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20executive%20order%20signed%20on%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office%2C%20Trump%20set%20out%20to%20end%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bradical%20and%20wasteful%26quot%3B%20DEI%20programs%20in%20the%20federal%20government.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20in%20a%20separate%20executive%20order%2C%20he%20revoked%20an%20order%20signed%20by%20President%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%20in%201965%20that%20barred%20government%20contractors%20and%20subcontractors%20from%20engaging%20in%20employment%20discrimination.%20Many%20government%20contractors%20are%20public%20companies.%20But%20even%20for%20those%20that%20aren't%2C%20the%20order%20lays%20out%20steps%20for%20%26quot%3Bencouraging%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20end%20illegal%20DEI%20discrimination%20and%20preferences.%26quot%3B%20It%20instructs%20federal%20agencies%20to%20identify%20up%20to%20nine%20potential%20civil%20compliance%20investigations%20of%20private%20companies.%20In%20effect%2C%20they're%20hunting%20for%20lists%20of%20names%20to%20sue%2C%20and%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20be%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20valid%20fear%20of%20companies%20having%20a%20target%20on%20their%20back%20based%20on%20how%20they%20outwardly%20promote%20DE%26amp%3BI%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Renai%20Rodney%2C%20a%20counsel%20in%20Ropes%20%26amp%3B%20Gray's%20litigation%20and%20enforcement%20practice%20group%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20unfortunate%2C%20because%20while%20there's%20certain%20things%20in%20the%20executive%20order%20that%20companies%20should%20certainly%20be%20mindful%20of%2C%20the%20underlying%20law%20has%20not%20changed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chaos%20and%20confusion%20is%20part%20of%20the%20point.%20The%20letter%20of%20the%20law%20isn't%20any%20different%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20always%20been%20illegal%20for%20companies%20to%20implement%20quotas%20or%20require%20a%20certain%20proportion%20of%20their%20workforce%20to%20be%20a%20specific%20race%20or%20gender.%20The%20law's%20interpretation%20and%20enforcement%2C%20however%2C%20have%20clearly%20undergone%20a%20reversal.%20Federal%20contractors%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20going%20after%20them%20to%20assert%20that%20their%20DEI%20policies%20violated%20the%20False%20Claims%20Act%2C%20which%20prohibits%20contractors%20from%20defrauding%20the%20federal%20government.%20Major%20companies%20could%20be%20accused%20by%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%20of%20violating%20Title%20VII%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%20of%201964%2C%20which%20prohibits%20employment%20discrimination%20based%20on%20race%2C%20color%2C%20religion%2C%20sex%2C%20and%20national%20origin.%20The%20law%20was%20meant%20to%20prevent%20businesses%20from%20declining%20to%20hire%20someone%20because%20they're%20part%20of%20a%20minority%20group%3B%20now%20it's%20being%20used%20against%20businesses%20by%20people%20who%20say%20they're%20being%20overlooked%20because%20they're%20in%20the%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenny%20Yang%2C%20who%20served%20as%20an%20EEOC%20chair%20and%20commissioner%20from%202013%20to%202018%20and%20now%20heads%20the%20Urban%20Institute's%20Workplace%20Equity%20Initiative%2C%20said%20companies%20facing%20claims%20that%20they%20discriminated%20or%20used%20ill-defined%20%26quot%3Billegal%20DEI%26quot%3B%20practices%20may%20very%20well%20have%20a%20good%20case%20in%20court%20and%20win.%20But%20going%20to%20court%20costs%20money%2C%20and%20any%20battle%20is%20likely%20to%20draw%20attention%2C%20so%20they%20may%20be%20inclined%20to%20give%20up%20before%20there's%20even%20a%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20this%20really%20does%20not%20have%20the%20law%20behind%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20likely%20to%20survive%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20companies%20don't%20want%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20even%20defending%20against%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20the%20reputational%20harm%2C%20or%20they%20don't%20want%20their%20board%20to%20get%20upset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20may%20proactively%20examine%20programs%20they%20think%20could%20be%20subject%20to%20legal%20scrutiny%2C%20such%20as%20scholarships%20or%20fellowships%20aimed%20at%20underrepresented%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20may%20not%20actually%20make%20it%20to%20a%20legal%20decision%2C%20but%20they%20decide%2C%20well%2C%20we'll%20settle%20this%20by%20opening%20up%20that%20program%20to%20everyone%20and%20not%20just%20groups%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodney%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20haven't%20been%20ruled%20unlawful%2C%20but%20companies%20are%20either%20deciding%20we%20don't%20want%20a%20bad%20decision%20on%20the%20books%20or%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20use%20resources%20to%20fight%20this%2C%20so%20we'll%20just%20change%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20isn't%20just%20the%20federal%20government%20that%20companies%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20%E2%80%94%20conservative%20state%20authorities%2C%20legal%20groups%2C%20and%20individuals%20with%20big%20platforms%20are%20also%20freaking%20them%20out.%20In%20mid-2024%2C%20Missouri's%20attorney%20general%20sued%20IBM%2C%20alleging%20that%20it%20was%20using%20unlawful%20racial%20and%20gender%20quotas%20in%20employment.%20The%20Trump-aligned%20group%20America%20First%20Legal%20has%20filed%20several%20complaints%2C%20including%20against%20Southwest%20Airlines%20and%20American%20Airlines%2C%20over%20their%20DEI%20practices.%20Texas'%20attorney%20general%2C%20Ken%20Paxton%2C%20has%20told%20financial%20institutions%20such%20as%20BlackRock%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20and%20Citigroup%20to%20watch%20it%20on%20DEI%20or%20face%20enforcement%20actions.%20A%20police%20pension%20fund%20in%20Florida%20is%20suing%20Target%2C%20saying%20it%20wasn't%20made%20aware%20of%20the%20risks%20of%20the%20retailer's%20DEI%20initiatives%20and%20potential%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20what's%20the%20actual%20legal%20risk%2C%20I%20think%20we're%20seeing%20it%20now%20morph%20into%20Title%20VII%20discrimination%20claims%20from%20individual%20employees%2C%20activism%20by%20Republican%20state%20attorneys%20general%2C%26quot%3B%20Baker%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20we're%20waiting%20to%20see%20exactly%20what%20comes%20out%20of%20the%20president's%20executive%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20companies%20quietly%20disappear%20mentions%20of%20their%20DEI%20policies%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20work%20can't%20continue.%20They%20can%20practice%20without%20preaching%2C%20and%20many%20will.%20If%20one%20is%20to%20believe%20companies%20meant%20it%20when%20they%20said%20they%20cared%20about%20fostering%20diverse%20workplaces%2C%20then%20presumably%20none%20of%20that%20went%20away%20overnight.%20The%20issue%20is%20that%2C%20cynically%2C%20it's%20sometimes%20hard%20to%20believe%20these%20companies%20were%20that%20dedicated%20to%20the%20idea%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20initiatives%20weren't%20always%20measurable%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20public%20commitments%20without%20really%20thinking%20through%20how%20they%20were%20measured%20and%20implemented.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20values%20often%20seem%20like%20a%20PR%20stunt%20%E2%80%94%20X%20supports%20the%20troops%2C%20Y%20wants%20to%20end%20racism%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20where%20companies%20calculate%20the%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20answer%20is%20at%20any%20given%20moment.%20What's%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20often%20means%20%26quot%3Bwhatever%20will%20generate%20the%20most%20cash%20for%20shareholders%26quot%3B%20or%2C%20increasingly%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20will%20keep%20us%20out%20of%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20governed%20by%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20governed%20by%20who%20was%20last%20yelling%20at%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20companies%20were%20worried%20about%20the%20progressive%20backlash.%20Now%20they're%20worried%20about%20the%20conservative%20one.%20To%20some%20extent%2C%20companies%20ended%20up%20in%20this%20spot%20by%20talking%20a%20big%20game%20and%20launching%20programs%20without%20thinking%20through%20what%20they%20were%20actually%20trying%20to%20accomplish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20making%20decisions%20out%20of%20fear%2C%20likely%2C%20but%20they%20know%20no%20matter%20what%20they%20do%2C%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20population%20that%20is%20upset%20with%20that%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Naomi%20Wheeless%2C%20the%20chief%20customer%20officer%20at%20Nextech%20Systems%20and%20a%20board%20member%20at%20Eventbrite.%20%26quot%3BSo%20moving%20silently%20or%20slowly%20is%20the%20strategy%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20are%20choosing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20is%20not%20a%20foolproof%20one.%20Many%20activists%20and%20government%20officials%20are%20out%20for%20blood%2C%20and%20they're%20seeking%20to%20make%20some%20high-profile%20examples%20of%20big-name%20companies%20in%20order%20to%20put%20some%20anxiety%20in%20everyone%20else.%20Hiding%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20won't%20be%20found.%20What's%20more%2C%20the%20political%20winds%20can%20change%2C%20and%20if%20they%20do%2C%20companies%20may%20be%20faced%20with%20explaining%20their%20choices%20to%20a%20new%20set%20of%20constituents.%20Maybe%20next%20time%20they'll%20think%20about%20what%20they%20actually%20want%20to%20accomplish%2C%20business-wise%2C%20instead%20of%20just%20paying%20lip%20service%20to%20whoever's%20maddest%20at%20them%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-policies-delete-trump-disney-general-motors-pepsi-diversity-target-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739438221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ad11937bb3f854015cb66b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-policies-delete-trump-disney-general-motors-pepsi-diversity-target-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20like%20Disney%2C%20General%20Motors%2C%20and%20Pepsico%20are%20quietly%20backing%20away%20from%20diversity%20initiatives%20and%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-policies-delete-trump-disney-general-motors-pepsi-diversity-target-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gummybear%20International%2C%20Toonz%20Unveil%20%E2%80%98Gummib%C3%A4r%20and%20Friends%2C%20Operation%20Cotton%20Candy%E2%80%99%20at%20EFM%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739438198000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FGummibar-and-Friends-Operation-Cotton-Candy.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%