0gig%20economy.%20While%20the%20cash-rich%2C%20time-poor%20have%20been%20sending%20their%20assistants%20ahead%20to%20get%20early%20access%20for%20years%2C%20more%20people%20are%20joining%20them%20in%20outsourcing%20their%20time.%20Bookings%20for%20professional%20standing%20line%20services%20on%20Taskrabbit%20experienced%20an%2018%25%20increase%20in%20the%20US%20in%20November%20and%20December%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20the%20company%20found%2C%20earning%20those%20willing%20to%20wait%20an%20average%20of%20%2427%20an%20hour.%20For%20people%20with%20more%20money%20than%20time%2C%20it's%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20save%20a%20few%20precious%20hours.%20For%20those%20who%20wait%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20bad%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20to%20become%20a%20line%20sitter%20is%20simple%3A%20Tanya%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20we%20just%20use%20her%20first%20name%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy%2C%20will%20get%20a%20notification%20saying%20someone%20is%20interested%20in%20hiring%20her%20to%20stand%20in%20line.%20After%20reviewing%20the%20details%20and%20making%20sure%20it%20is%20something%20she%20can%20do%2C%20she%20will%20contact%20the%20client%20and%20ask%20for%20specifics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20restaurants%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flucali-most-legendary-pizza-place-brooklyn-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epizzeria%20Lucali%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Brooklyn%20%E2%80%94%20which%20saw%20a%2030%25%20increase%20in%20bookings%20the%20month%20after%20Taylor%20Swift%20and%20Travis%20Kelce%20made%20an%20appearance%20%E2%80%94%20only%20take%20in-person%20reservations%2C%20leading%20to%20long%20wait%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20know%20how%20many%20people%20they%20have%20in%20their%20party%20and%20what%20time%20they%20would%20like%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanya%20says.%20The%20first%20people%20in%20line%20for%20a%20popular%20spot%20typically%20show%20up%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20before%20a%20host%20comes%20out%20to%20take%20reservations.%20When%20it's%20Tanya's%20turn%20at%20the%20front%20she%20will%20tell%20the%20host%20the%20client's%20preferred%20timings%20for%20later%20that%20evening.%20%26quot%3BI%20also%20always%20ask%20for%20alternative%20times%20because%20you%20never%20know%20where%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20until%20you're%20up%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%20The%20client%20then%20comes%20back%20at%20the%20reserved%20time%20to%20claim%20their%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETanya%20quickly%20learned%20that%20different%20lines%20have%20different%20protocols.%20Waiting%20for%20Broadway%20tickets%20or%20an%20art%20gallery%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20waiting%20in%20line%20at%20a%20popular%20restaurant.%20For%20%26quot%3Bthe%20really%20sought-after%20places%20like%20Lucali%20and%20Don%20Angie%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20she's%20started%20charging%20a%20two-hour%20minimum%20for%20clients%20to%20have%20a%20shot%20at%20a%20reservation.%20If%20clients%20don't%20want%20to%20fork%20out%20for%20the%20extra%20hours%20to%20guarantee%20a%20front-of-line%20spot%2C%20Tanya%20can't%20make%20any%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%20a%20client%20insisted%20that%20Tanya%20start%20waiting%20for%20a%20reservation%20at%20Lucali%20at%203%20p.m.%2C%20an%20hour%20before%20reservations%20are%20taken.%20She%20didn't%20end%20up%20getting%20the%20reservation.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20disappointed%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanya%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bhesitated%20to%20pay.%26quot%3B%20But%20she%20has%20never%20been%20stiffed%20for%20failing%20to%20get%20a%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20places%20the%20process%20is%20very%20predictable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIn%20other%20places%2C%20you%20have%20no%20idea%20whether%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20a%20spot%20or%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETanya%20charges%20%2420%20an%20hour.%20Clients%20will%20generally%20book%20a%20day%20or%20two%20in%20advance%2C%20but%20sometimes%20she%20will%20activate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-made-6-figures-taskrabbit-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esame-day%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20take%20on%20last-minute%20requests.%20She%20normally%20makes%20herself%20available%20on%20Friday%20nights%20and%20weekends%2C%20averaging%20about%20three-line-standing%20bookings%20a%20week%20and%20earning%20between%20%2460%20and%20%24200.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20one%20of%20my%20most%20consistent%20task%20categories%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanya%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20relatively%20easy%2C%20but%20then%20it's%20not.%20You%20do%20have%20to%20have%20patience%20and%20you%20do%20have%20to%20come%20prepared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20longest%20line%20to%20date%20was%20for%20tickets%20to%20Gutenberg!%20The%20Musical!%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-musical-movies-based-on-broadway-shows-and-worst-films-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBroadway%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20limited%20engagement%20and%20it%20was%20closing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20really%20going%20crazy%20trying%20to%20get%20these%20tickets.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20January%202024%20and%20one%20of%20the%20coldest%20days%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20client%20had%20paid%20for%20her%20to%20stand%20in%20line%20from%206%20a.m.%20until%20the%20box%20office%20opened%20at%20noon.%20Other%20people%20didn't%20start%20showing%20up%20until%209%3A30.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20freezing%2C%20it%20was%20brutal.%20It%20tested%20everything%20I%20had%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Despite%20wearing%20two%20coats%2C%20two%20hats%2C%20a%20scarf%2C%20and%20two%20pairs%20of%20gloves%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20even%20feel%20my%20hands%20or%20my%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20wait%20slightly%20less%20gruelling%20Tanya%20brought%20a%20stool%20to%20sit%20on%20to%20and%20a%20hot%20drink%20to%20sip%20on.%20She%20also%20listened%20to%20a%20high-energy%20playlist%20she%20had%20compiled%20specifically%20for%20these%20types%20of%20gigs%2C%20featuring%20hits%20from%20The%20Greatest%20Showman%2C%20Michael%20Jackson%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeyonce-wins-grammys-album-of-the-year-cowboy-carter-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeyonc%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20last%20thing%20I%20would%20listen%20to%20is%20something%20really%20slow%20that%20makes%20me%20sleepy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20The%20client%2C%20a%20local%20New%20Yorker%2C%20met%20her%20in%20the%20line%20shortly%20before%20noon%20so%20that%20they%20could%20both%20purchase%20the%20two-ticket-limit%20each.%20On%20top%20of%20%24120%20for%20standing%20in%20line%2C%20they%20gave%20Tanya%20a%20%2450%20tip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EProfessional%20line-standing%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20New%20York.%20Jennifer%20Goff%2C%2038%2C%20first%20tried%20her%20hand%20at%20making%20some%20money%20from%20waiting%20in%20line%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgame-of-thrones-movie-help-warner-bros-discovery-underperform-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGame%20of%20Thrones%3C%2Fa%3E%20pop-up%20bar%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20in%202017.%20After%20three%20hours%20of%20trying%20to%20convince%20those%20already%20in%20the%20queue%20to%20hire%20her%20to%20stand%20in%20for%20them%20while%20they%20went%20for%20a%20drink%20or%20grabbed%20some%20food%2C%20someone%20bit.%20From%20there%2C%20standing%20in%20line%20snowballed%20into%20a%20full-time%20business.%20She%20launched%20Skip%20The%20Line%2C%20which%20now%20employs%20five%20people%20part-time%20and%20charges%20%2430%20to%20%2440%20an%20hour%20for%20their%20services.%20Goff%20has%20stood%20in%20line%20for%20concerts%2C%20book%20signings%2C%20new%20iPhones%2C%20and%20releases%20of%20limited-edition%20liquors.%20However%2C%20her%20most%20lucrative%20jobs%20are%20standing%20in%20line%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-trump-musk-defy-court-ruling-constitution-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20hearings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20generally%20only%20allow%20the%20first%2050%20people%20in%20line%20to%20attend%20the%20oral%20arguments%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20people%20do%20have%20to%20line%20up%2C%20sometimes%20for%20days.%26quot%3B%20In%20November%2C%20she%20was%20booked%20to%20stand%20in%20line%2024%20hours%20in%20advance%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F23%2F23-477%2F288875%2F20231106135238432_U.S.%2520v.%2520Skrmetti%2520-%2520Pet.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20v%20Skrmetti%3C%2Fa%3E%20Supreme%20Court%20hearings%2C%20which%20dealt%20with%20whether%20minors%20could%20receive%20gender-affirming%20care.%20In%202023%2C%20she%20was%20booked%2036%20hours%20in%20advance%20to%20secure%20a%20spot%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-january-6-election-ruling-decision-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20States%20v.%20Donald%20J.%20Trump%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehearings%2C%20which%20addressed%20presidential%20immunity.%20For%20bookings%20of%20this%20length%2C%20Goff's%20team%20will%20work%20in%20shifts%20that%20range%20from%20about%20four%20to%20eight%20hours%20at%20a%20time.%20If%20they%20need%20to%20quickly%20grab%20a%20snack%20or%20use%20the%20bathroom%2C%20other%20members%20of%20Goff's%20team%20will%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20their%20spot.%20For%20both%20cases%2C%20she%20got%20her%20clients%20seats%20in%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoff%20has%20found%20that%20others%20in%20the%20line%20are%20interested%20in%20hearing%20about%20her%20services.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20popular%20topic%20of%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20standing%20in%20line%20for%20a%20very%20lo