rth%20quarter%2C%20a%2039%25%20year-over-year%20increase%20but%20below%20Wall%20Street%20analysts'%20estimates%20of%20103.8%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUser%20growth%20is%20a%20critical%20metric%20for%20Reddit%20because%20so%20much%20of%20its%20business%20relies%20on%20advertising.%C2%A0Before%20the%20company%20went%20public%20in%20March%2C%20Reddit%20said%20in%20a%20filing%20that%20it%20generates%20%26quot%3Bsubstantially%20all%20of%20our%20revenue%20from%20advertising.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20reported%20%24428%20million%20in%20revenue%20for%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20a%2071%25%20year-over-year%20increase%20from%202023.%20About%2092%25%20of%20that%20fourth-quarter%20revenue%20came%20from%20advertising.%20The%20rest%20came%20from%20Reddit's%20%26quot%3Bother%20revenue%26quot%3B%20segment%2C%20which%20includes%20content%20licensing%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-google-search-ceo-steve-huffman-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Huffman%2C%20Reddit's%20CEO%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20an%20earnings%20call%20that%20it's%20become%20common%20for%20people%20to%20use%20search%20engines%20like%20Google%20to%20peruse%20Reddit.%20But%20Huffman%20said%20the%20site%20saw%20%26quot%3Bvolatility%26quot%3B%20in%20traffic%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%C2%A0after%20Google%20tweaked%20its%20search%20algorithm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuffman%20said%20he%20was%20not%20worried%20about%20the%20traffic%20volatility%20and%20that%20it%20did%20not%20impact%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20feel%20very%20good%20about%20the%20pace%20that%20we're%20on%20from%20Q1%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20volatility%20from%20Google%20all%20the%20time%2C%20as%20does%20everybody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20after%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuffman%20said%20during%20the%20call%20that%20the%20algorithm%20change%20primarily%20impacted%20%26quot%3Blogged-out%20users%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Epeople%20browsing%20Reddit%20without%20an%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELogged-in%20user%20numbers%20grew%2027%25%20in%202024%2C%C2%A0the%20company%20said%20in%20its%20earnings%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20also%20said%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-google-search-ceo-steve-huffman-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20search%20queries%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20include%20%26quot%3BReddit%26quot%3B%20increased%2C%20suggesting%20more%20users%20are%20seeking%20answers%20from%20the%20thread-based%20platform.%20The%20company%20moved%20away%20from%20forcing%20searchers%20to%20download%20the%20Reddit%20app%20and%20began%20showing%20all%20public%20posts%2C%20even%20to%20logged-out%20users%2C%20Huffman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20said%C2%A0the%20solution%20to%20gaining%20loyal%20users%C2%A0is%20building%20tools%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-answers-how-it-works-performs-early-access-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20Answers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20AI-powered%20search%20tool%20that%20generates%20answers%20based%20on%20input%20from%20users%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20has%20made%20a%20number%20of%20AI-related%20investments%20and%20partnerships%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20announced%20a%20content%20licensing%20deal%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-comments-ai-training-models-google-openai-jen-wong-huffman-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20and%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20the%20makers%20of%20Gemini%20and%20ChatGPT%20to%20train%20their%20models%20on%20Reddit%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20much%20those%20deals%20contributed%20to%20Reddit's%20revenue.%20Google%20is%20paying