S%20militants.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Trump%20admin%20is%20weighing%20withdrawing%20these%20forces%2C%20and%20the%20Russian%20military%20is%20losing%20its%20access.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20now%20hangs%20on%20by%20its%20fingertips%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Syria%20expert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESyria%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20complex%20proxy%20fights%20since%20its%20civil%20war%20broke%20out%20in%202011%2C%20but%20who%20holds%20power%20and%20where%20is%20now%20shifting%20rapidly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20change%20came%20from%20the%20dramatic%20toppling%20of%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20regime%20in%20December.%20It%20was%20driven%20out%20by%20the%20Islamist%20group%20Hayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%2C%20who%20are%20no%20friends%20of%20Russia%20or%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHTS%20holds%20territory%20from%20Aleppo%20in%20the%20northwest%20to%20Damascus%2C%20the%20seat%20of%20the%20Assad%20regime.%20But%20Syria%20remains%20fractured%20by%20competing%20armies.%20Turkish%20forces%20and%20militants%20it%20backs%20hold%20pockets%20near%20its%20northern%20border.%20The%20US-partnered%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20occupy%20the%20large%20triangle%20of%20northeastern%20Syria%2C%20an%20area%20that%20has%20oilfields%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-kurdish-partners-still-guarding-isis-prisoners-in-syria-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprison%20camps%3C%2Fa%3E%20holding%20ISIS%20fighters.%20Russia%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-ships-arrived-naval-base-tartus-syria-move-equipment-images-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereducing%20its%20military%20footprint%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Israel%20seizes%20new%20positions%20near%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%20But%20the%20newest%20question%20mark%20is%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%202%2C000%20troops%20in%20Syria%20backing%20the%20Kurdish-led%20SDF%20to%20contain%20ISIS.%20It%20also%20controls%